table:table-cell.text:p: This tab describes the configuration metadata. The actual configuration data are specificed in the tabs “input” and “output”.
Its content goes inside the Genericode (GC) element <Identification/>
Interoperability Solutions for Public Administrations, programme
This sheet declares the variables needed for the end-to-end execution of the whole pipeline.
The UBL version used for the generation of this distribution package.
The UBL version immediately prior to the one used for the generation of the W3C schemas.
Override this as "no" for UBL 2.2 and earlier.
Timestamp of the Cranesoftwrights' utilities for the transformation of the BIE components expressed as Genericode into W3C XSD schemas.
Timestamp of the Cranesoftwrights' utilities for the transformation of the ODS Spreadsheets containing the models into Genericode.
Timestamp of the Cranesoftwrights' utilities for the transformation of he Context Value Association and Genericode files into XM Stylesheets.
Timestamp of the Cranesoftwrights' utilities for the transformation of he Context Value Association files into Schematron files.
Timestamp of the Cranesoftwrights' utilities for the re-generation of the ods files from the Genericode files containing the BIE components.
Timestamp of the everis-sembu's utilities for the generation of the blyter configuration files into Genericode, JSON and RDF formats.
Input folders and file path names
This tab is used to specify which folders and files are needed before executing the application.
Inputs for one or more steps of the pipeline or needed to configure the application.
Skeleton and constant files, i.e. those files that are needed to deploy the application, regardless of the configuration.
Location of the model. In UBL models are maintained as spread-sheets-
Metadata for the identification of the BIE(s), namespaces, UBLversion, etc.
Long ODS tabs names need to be shortened at edition time, in the ods, and spanned at GC generation time.
Location of input gc files, e.g. previous version of the UBL-Entitites as gc files.
Utilities directory with XSL-T and everis-sembu files.
The default UBL configuration file for this model.
To check the spelling of the words in the model.
File containing the abbreviated and non-abbreviated correspondance names of the ods tabs.
Main XSL-T file for the transformation of the ods files into Genericode files.
Main XSL-T file used to check the conformance of the BIE components, in the GC file, to the UBL Naming and Design Rules (NDR).
Main XSL-T file used to generate the XSD files.
Ouput folders and file path names
This tab is used to specify the folders containing the automatically produced files.
Location for any temporal or final distribution folder and files generated automatically.
The final distribution folders and files.
